\noindent WebRAG benefits from non-EN information and LLMs. We noticed that Bing search sometimes retrieves noisy passages together with relevant passages that are in languages other than English, particularly for subject entities from non-English demographic regions. In such cases, the LLM is still able to generate temporally relevant responses in English based on the non-English passages (ex.2 in Table (ref)). This gives WebRAG an advantage over others, as the news streams we employed are exclusively in English.